Package org.sbml.jsbml

Interface SBMLInputConverter<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of input model that can be treated by this converter.

    public interface SBMLInputConverter<T>
    This interface allows the implementing class to create a JSBML model based on some other data structure. Possible examples are CellDesigner plug-in data structures or Objects from libSBML. Other data structures can also be considered, such as a conversion of BioPax or CellML into JSBML data structures.
    Since:
    0.8
    Author:
    Andreas Dräger

        T getOriginalModel​()
        Returns:
        The original model that has been converted by this class in the method convertModel(Object). Typically, the identical result can also be obtained by calling AbstractTreeNode.getUserObject(Object) with ORIGINAL_MODEL_KEY as parameter.
